11/10/2006
BELGRADE, Serbia -- Prosecutors on Tuesday (October 10th) officially charged retired Serbia-Montenegro Army officer Blagoje Govedarica with helping war crimes fugitive Ratko Mladic evade arrest. 
Govedarica was arrested about six months ago during a crackdown on suspected Mladic supporters. 
In all, 11 people, including several former Yugoslav and Republika Srpska officers, were detained for allegedly helping Mladic hide in Belgrade between June 2002 and January 2006. 
(Danas - 11/10/06)
